how equal the lines spread apart were to eachother
The strategy I used is looking out for which diagram had more erratic an unpredictable lines thus proving that the diagram is undergoing more stress than the other one.
Determining which network lines are clustered the most in an area

when picking which diagram had the least stress, I often found the one with the most stress and then worked backwards. I did this by seeing which one had the most connections within a tight nexus with a few outliers branching out wildly far. failing that, I found which ever nexus was tighter, with the most nodes in the smallest area. the diagrams with the nodes spread out mostly equally often had the least stress.
Number of points on outer perimeter and the average length of the connection when compared to diagram 2, with a quick judgement made on gut feeling.
